==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
In the oracle bone script, it was {{Han compound|黍|口|ls=ic|nocap=1|t1=glutinous millet|t2=mouth}}. The whole character perhaps indicate that millet was used to produce liquor from fermentation which could be drank and/or sacrificed.

In the seal script, the {{zh-l|*口}} was replaced with the related {{zh-l|*甘|sweet}}. Hence, the most conservative variant is [[𪏽]].

Currently, the {{zh-l|*黍}} has simplified into {{zh-l|*禾}} and the form of the bottom component {{zh-l|*甘}} has become akin to the unrelated {{zh-l|*曰}}.

